p: The 1H and 13C NMR signals of 1 (see Table 2) were assigned based on thorough analysis of COSY, HSQC, and HMBC spectra presented in the Supplementary Materials. The 1H NMR spectrum showed signals at δ H 2.47 (d, J = 14.5 Hz) and δ H 2.30 (d, J = 14.5 Hz) referring to diastereotopic hydrogens H-9 and H-9’. At δ H 5.76 (dd, J = 9.4, 5.3 Hz), a double doublet signal corresponds to the methynic hydrogen H-2. Four methyl groups were observed with displacements at δ H 1.79 (s, H-12 or H-13), δ H 1.94 (d, J = 1.6 Hz, H-12 or H-13), δ H 1.04 (s, H-14), and at δ H 1.85 (s, H-15).
